ZH: 请大家站定，我们要开始上课了。
EN: Please stand still, we are about to start the class.

ZH: 雨下得太大了，我只能站定等雨停。
EN: The rain is so heavy that I can only stand still and wait for it to stop.

ZH: 老师在台上讲课时，学生们都站定了。
EN: When the teacher was giving a lecture, all the students stood still.

ZH: 这里是警察局，请你站定，不要乱动。
EN: This is a police station, please stand still and don't move.

ZH: 站定后，抬头看到了美丽的星空。
EN: After standing still, I looked up and saw the beautiful starry sky.

ZH: 他站定在那里，看着远方的车辆。
EN: He stood still there, watching the vehicles in the distance.

ZH: 小狗站定不动，好像在等主人回家。
EN: The puppy stood still, as if waiting for its owner to come home.

ZH: 在飞机起飞之前，请所有乘客都站定。
EN: Before takeoff, please have all passengers stand still.

ZH: 队伍站定后，开始进行晨练活动。
EN: After the team stood still, they started the morning exercise.

ZH: 在跑步机上跑步时，请保持站定的姿势。
EN: When running on the treadmill, please maintain a standing position.

ZH: 他站定在山顶，俯瞰着美丽的风景。
EN: He stood still at the top of the mountain, overlooking the beautiful scenery.

ZH: 指挥员大声命令士兵们站定不动。
EN: The commander loudly ordered the soldiers to stand still.

ZH: 过马路时，请站定在人行横道线上。
EN: When crossing the road, please stand still on the pedestrian crossing.

ZH: 请大家在海滩上站定，等待指示。
EN: Please stand still on the beach and wait for instructions.

ZH: 在观看游行时，观众们站定以示敬意。
EN: When watching the parade, the audience stood still as a sign of respect.

ZH: 这个动作需要你站定一个小时，以锻炼腿部肌肉。
EN: This exercise requires you to stand still for an hour to exercise your leg muscles.

ZH: 当拍摄照片时，请大家站定并保持微笑。
EN: When taking photos, please stand still and maintain a smile.

ZH: 警察停下了车子，示意司机站定不要动。
EN: The police stopped the car and signaled the driver to stand still and not move.

ZH: 在购物中心逛街时，请不要站定在楼梯口。
EN: When shopping in a mall, please do not stand still at the staircase.

ZH: 请在开始比赛前站定在起跑线上。
EN: Please stand still on the starting line before the race begins.
